promptInjection:
CAPABILITY: Email Sending via /api/proxy/email

OVERVIEW:
- Generated apps can send emails through the VibeTree email proxy backed by Resend.
- Emails always send FROM apps@vibetree.app — you cannot change the from address.
- No attachments are supported — plain text (body) or HTML (html) only.
- Costs 0.1 credits per email. Rate limit: 50 per user per day.

ENDPOINT:
  POST kApiBaseURL + "/api/proxy/email"

REQUEST HEADERS:
  Content-Type: application/json
  X-App-Token: kAppToken

REQUEST BODY (JSON):
  {
    "to": "recipient@example.com",   // Required: recipient email
    "subject": "Your RSVP Confirmed", // Required: email subject
    "body": "Thanks for signing up!", // Plain text content (use this OR html)
    "html": "<p>Thanks!</p>",         // HTML content (optional, use instead of body)
    "userId": kUserId                 // Required: the current user's ID for billing
  }

RESPONSE:
  { "success": true, "messageId": "abc123" }   // on success
  { "error": "...", "required": 0.1 }          // on insufficient credits (HTTP 402)
  { "error": "Daily email limit reached..." }  // on rate limit (HTTP 429)

SWIFT PATTERN:

func sendConfirmationEmail(to: String, subject: String, body: String) async {
    guard let url = URL(string: kApiBaseURL + "/api/proxy/email") else { return }
    var request = URLRequest(url: url)
    request.httpMethod = "POST"
    request.setValue("application/json", forHTTPHeaderField: "Content-Type")
    request.setValue(kAppToken, forHTTPHeaderField: "X-App-Token")
    let payload: [String: Any] = [
        "to": to,
        "subject": subject,
        "body": body,
        "userId": kUserId
    ]
    request.httpBody = try? JSONSerialization.data(withJSONObject: payload)
    do {
        let (data, response) = try await URLSession.shared.data(for: request)
        if let http = response as? HTTPURLResponse, http.statusCode == 200 {
            print("Email sent successfully")
        } else if let http = response as? HTTPURLResponse, http.statusCode == 402 {
            // Show user a credits-insufficient message
            print("Insufficient credits to send email")
        } else {
            print("Email send failed:", String(data: data, encoding: .utf8) ?? "unknown")
        }
    } catch {
        print("Email request error:", error)
    }
}

USE CASES:
- RSVP / event registration confirmation: send a summary of what the user signed up for.
- Booking confirmation: send appointment details (date, time, service).
- Contact form submission: forward user message to the app owner's email.
- Welcome email: greet new users after they create an account.
- Reminder email: send a reminder before an event or deadline (trigger on a date/time action in-app).

ANTI-PATTERNS:
- Do NOT attempt to set a custom from address — it is always apps@vibetree.app.
- Do NOT include attachments or file data — plain text or HTML only.
- Do NOT call Resend or any other email API directly — always go through /api/proxy/email.
- Do NOT send emails without user intent or confirmation — always send in response to an explicit user action (button tap, form submit, etc.).
- Do NOT display the raw JSON error to the user — show a friendly message like 'Could not send email. Please try again.'
